e through the thickness, within the material-safe range.","qualityGoalMeaning_minimum_char":"For wood and MDF, keeps heat shallower and reminds you that air assist and speed matter.","qualityGoalMeaning_minimum_melting":"For acrylic and plastics, reduces excess heat at the entry and warns about speed and power.","qualityGoalMeaning_polished_acrylic_edge":"For thicker acrylic, favors a controlled upper-third focus but still requires a flame and haze check.","qualityGoalMeaning_best_dimensional_accuracy":"Prioritizes measured kerf and real fit over focus theory alone.","qualityGoalMeaning_press_fit_accuracy":"Prioritizes slot/tab calibration, clearance, and the face that controls assembly.","qualityGoalMeaning_fast_production":"Warns that faster settings can invalidate kerf calibration unless tested at production speed.","qualityGoalMeaning_safe_mirror_backing":"Keeps focus shallower and requires a scrap test because the backing can dominate the result.","calibrationModeMeaning_multi_line_strip":"Cut several parallel lines in a known strip; kerf is calculated from the lost width divided by the cut-line count.","calibrationModeMeaning_outside_square":"Cut an outside square and compare its real outside size with the CAD size.","calibrationModeMeaning_inside_hole":"Cut an internal hole and compare the measured opening with the CAD hole size.","calibrationModeMeaning_slot_tab_fit":"Cut matching slots and tabs to measure fit, clearance, and which face controls the assembly.","calibrationModeMeaning_inlay_fit":"Cut mating inlay pieces and judge whether the visible face closes cleanly without forcing.","calibrationModeMeaning_focus_ladder":"Cut or mark a ladder at several focus depths so the best edge, char, and fit can be chosen from real samples.","helpTopKerf":"Top kerf is measured on the entry face. Use it when the visible top edge controls fit or appearance.","helpBottomKerf":"Bottom kerf is measured on the exit face. Use it when parts fit from the underside or taper is important.","helpAverageKerf":"Average kerf is useful for general offsets, but do not hide taper if top and bottom kerf differ.","helpDesignedWidth":"Designed width is the CAD width before cutting. It is used with the measured coupon width to estimate kerf.","helpMeasuredWidth":"Measured width is the real coupon or feature size after cutting with the same settings.","helpCutLines":"Cut lines is the number of cut paths in the strip test. More lines reduce measurement noise.","helpJsonData":"Export JSON to move saved profiles to another browser or import calibrated profiles back into this app.","helpLightBurnNotes":"Copy these notes into LightBurn or a job sheet so focus, kerf, optical profile, and warnings travel with the file.","noteSpeciesCalibration":"Species-specific calibration required.","notePaperFocus":"Focus is less critical than hold-down, air assist, and scorching control.","noteLeatherIdentify":"Identify tanning and finish first.","noteSwatchMandatory":"Swatch test mandatory.","noteSwatchOdorMandatory":"Swatch and odor test mandatory.","noteNearestPreset":"Thickness is outside the preset table; nearest preset was adapted.","noteEntryFaceEnergy":"Keep energy near the entry face.","noteWiderScore":"Use -0.5 to -1.0 mm for a wider visible score.","noteSmoothFill":"Defocus only when smoother fill is more important than sharpness.","notePhotoFill":"Defocus reduces detail but can smooth tonal fill.","notePolishedAcrylic":"Watch flame, haze, boiling, and extraction on polished acrylic edges.","noteKerfControlsFit":"Kerf calibration controls fit more than focus theory.","noteProductionInvalidates":"Speed and power changes can invalidate kerf calibration.","noteMirrorBacking":"Mirror backing needs a scrap test and shallow focus bias.","noteSurfaceChemistry":"Surface chemistry may dominate focus behavior. Run coating scrap test before production.","warningUnknownMaterialRisk":"Material identity is unknown. Do not laser cut until the material is confirmed safe by SDS or supplier documentation.","warningUnsafeFocus":"Never let focus optimization make unsafe materials seem safe.","warningMirrorAcrylicSeparate":"Treat mirror acrylic separately from normal acrylic.","warningPlainPmmaKerf":"Do not reuse plain PMMA kerf blindly.","warningMirrorBackingDamage":"Backing / coating can dominate the result and too much heat can damage it.","warningMdfPlywoodExtraction":"MDF and plywood need sufficient extraction.","warningLeatherTanning":"Chrome-tanned or unknown leather can be unsafe. Confirm tanning first.","warningFabricSds":"Unknown coated or synthetic fabrics require SDS/supplier confirmation.","warningAcrylicSupervision":"Acrylic cutting needs supervision and extraction.","warningTaperedKerf":"Measured kerf is tapered. Use the face that controls your assembly as the reference.","behaviorOpticalIndicator":"Beam diameter is an optical indicator only. Actual kerf depends on material absorption, melting, plume shielding, air assist, extraction, resin, density, backing films, lens cleanliness, alignment, and beam quality.","behaviorBottomWider":"Bottom optical diameter trends wider than the top at this focus.","behaviorBalanced":"Top and bottom optical diameters are relatively balanced at this focus.","benefitFirstLadder":"Use the recommendation as the first ladder test, not as final production proof.","riskInlayKerf":"Inlay and press-fit work require measured top, bottom, and average kerf.","confidenceBlocked":"Material is blocked until identity and safety are confirmed.","confidenceWeighted":"{confidence} confidence: preset match, optical profile, material risk, and kerf calibration were weighted together.","ladderTopSurface":"top surface","ladderUpperThird":"upper third"},"legal":{"owner":"Owner: Pnevma","backToTools":"Back to tools","privacy":{"title":"Privacy Policy","subtitle":"Compact privacy information for the local Pnevma Tools web app.","sections":[{"title":"Data processed locally","body":["Calculator values are used to produ